  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Accountant",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Review and authorize Accounts Receivable (AR) and Accounts Payable (AP) invoices, staff claims, and payment vouchers to ensure accuracy and compliance with company policies.</li>\n  <li>Maintain accurate and up-to-date accounting records for all outlets, including sales reconciliation and expense tracking.</li>\n  <li>Oversee month-end and year-end closing processes, including journal entries, accruals, and reconciliations.</li>\n  <li>Prepare financial consolidation, management reports, and statutory financial statements in accordance with Singapore Financial Reporting Standards (SFRS).</li>\n  <li>Handle GST submission, corporate tax computation, and deferred tax reporting, ensuring compliance with IRAS requirements.</li>\n  <li>Monitor cash flow, bank balances, and intercompany transactions, and prepare cash flow forecasts.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with external auditors, tax agents, and regulatory authorities on audit and compliance matters.</li>\n  <li>Support the budgeting and forecasting process, including variance analysis and cost control recommendations.</li>\n  <li>Review and analyse profit and loss statements to identify trends, discrepancies, and improvement opportunities.</li>\n  <li>Assist in setting up and improving internal controls, accounting procedures, and system enhancements.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with operations and HR departments on payroll verification, inventory reporting, and other finance-related activities.</li>\n  <li>Provide ad hoc financial analysis, reports, and support for management decisions.</li>\n</ul>",
